Question

 

What do good work health and safety practices achieve?

Your answer:

Correct answer: All of the above

Question

 

How can you ensure you are informed of WHS laws?

Your answer:

Correct answer: All of the above

Question

 

What is true in relation to workplace safety?

Your answer:

Correct answer: Everyone within the workplace has an active role to play

Question

 

What is NOT an objective of the WHS Act?

Your answer:

Correct answer: Facilitate a segmented, state-by-state approach to work health and safety laws

Question

 

What is a health and safety representative?

Your answer:

Correct answer: A worker who represents a group of workers in WHS matters

Question

 

Who bears the primary duty of care for work health and safety?

Your answer:

Correct answer: PCBUs

Question

 

What does the term reasonably practicable mean?

Your answer:

Correct answer: A duty holder must, within reason, do what they can at a particular time to ensure the health and safety of others

Question

 

A particular duty can only be imposed on one person. True or false?

Your answer:

Correct answer: False

Question

 

When can you contract out of a duty?

Your answer:

Correct answer: You can never contract out of a duty

Question

 

Which parties have an obligation to consult with each other?

Your answer:

Correct answer: People who owe duties in relation to the same matter must consult, cooperate and coordinate with each other

Question

 

If a PCBU cannot resolve a WHS issue with his or her workers, what party may the regulator appoint?

Your answer:

Correct answer: Health and safety inspector

Question

 

Complete the sentence. When consulting with workers, a PCBU is NOT required to…

Your answer:

Correct answer: … take all actions recommended by the workers

Question

 

Which is true about the duty to consult with others?

Your answer:

Correct answer: If people share a duty to the same matter, they must consult, cooperate and coordinate, so far as is reasonably practicable, with each other

Question

 

Complete the sentence. To eliminate or minimise risks in the workplace, you can…

Your answer:

Correct answer: … report any potential risks in the workplace

Question

 

What can you do to minimise risk in the workplace?

Your answer:

Correct answer: Comply with any directions and safety information, and make sure others do too
